KAMPALA , April 7 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Uganda is monitoring all imported products from Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy -LRB- BSE -RRB- -hit countries to prevent the BSE -caused mad cow disease from spreading to people and the cattle industry .
According to the local daily New Vision today , a national task force on BSE has also been set up to coordinate with international organizations and to advise government on policy concerning the disease .
Winyi Kaboyo , Assistant Commissioner for Veterinary Public Health in the Ministry of Health , was quoted as saying that government was carrying out public education to explain its policy in order to avoid misinformation and anxiety among the people .
The mad cow disease is associated with a transmissible agent consumed by cattle in concentrate feeds containing meat and bone meal .
It was first reported in Britain in 1986 and increased dramatically over the last ten years .
<ENAMEX TYPE="VITAL">Over 163,000 BSE -infected animals have been found in Britain ever since with 244 in Switzerland and a few others in nine other countries .</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">None BSE case has been reported in Uganda or any other African country .</ENAMEX>
BSE causes serious nervous disorders and eventually death .
There is no known cure yet .
